            "question": {
                "text": "A Boolean digital circuit is composed using two 4-\ninput multiplexers (M1 and M2) and one 2-input \nmultiplexer (M3) as shown in the figure. X0-X7 are \nthe inputs of the multiplexers M1 and M2 and could \nbe connected to either 0 or 1. The select lines of the \nmultiplexers are connected to Boolean variables A, B \nand C as shown. \n\n\nWhich one of the following set of values of (X0, X1, \nX2, X3, X4, X5, X6, X7) will realise the Boolean \nfunction A +A .C +A.B .C ?",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            },
            "options": [
                {
                    "id": "A",
                    "text": "(1, 1, 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0)",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "B",
                    "text": "(1, 1, 0, 0, 1, 1, 0, 1)",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "C",
                    "text": "(1, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0)",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "D",
                    "text": "(0, 0, 1, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1)",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "C"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "Given function f (ABC) = A\nAC\nAB C\n+\n+\n\n• \nFirst, we minimize the given function \nf (ABC) =\n(\n)(\n)\n(\n)\nA\nA\nAB C\nB\nB\nC\nC\nB\nB C\n+\n+\n+\n+\n+\n\n\nf (ABC) = \nAB\nB C+\n +\nAB\nC\nA\nABC\nABC\nC\nABC\nABC\n+\n+\n+\n+\n\nf (ABC) = AB\nB C+\n +\nC\nA\nABC\nABC\nABC\nABC\n+\n+\n+\n\n        f (ABC) = m (0, 1, 2, 3, 5) \n\nNow implementing on 2 \\times 1 mux. \n\n\n\n\n (X0 X1 X2 X3 X4 X5 X6 X7) = (11011100) \n\nHence correct answer is option (c).",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
